\int x^ne^{-x^2} dx= {-1\over 2} (x^n-1)e^{-x^2} + {n-1\over 2} \int (x^n-1)e^{-x^2}dx
u=\mathrm{e}^{-x^2}
\mathrm{d}v = x^n \ \mathrm{d}x
\mathrm{d}u=-2x\mathrm{e}^{-x^2} \ \mathrm{d}x
v= \frac{1}{n+1}x^{n+1}
\int u \ \mathrm{d}v = uv - \int v \ \mathrm{d}u 
du=e^{-x^2}x\ dx, u=-\frac 12 e^{-x^2}, v=x^{n-1}, dv=(n-1)x^{n-2}\ dx
\int x^ne^{-x^2}dx=-\frac 12x^{n-1}e^{-x^2}+\frac 12(n-1)\int x^{n-2}e^{-x^2}dx
